Aggregate Correlations.title: Aggregate Correlations
Aggregate Correlations.tooltip: Examination of the likely effects of a predictor variable on an outcome variable on average for the entire population

App Builder.title: App Builder
App Builder.tooltip: The App Builder allows anyone to create their own digital health app in minutes without any coding.  Their application can then also be built and released on iOS, Android, and as a Chrome browser extension.

Applications.title: Applications
Applications.tooltip: Get the settings for your application configurable at https://builder.quantimo.do

Collaborators.title: Collaborators
Collaborators.tooltip: Collaborators are allowed to modify settings for applications created at https://builder.quantimo.do.

Common Tags.title: Common Tags
Common Tags.tooltip: Variable tags are used to infer the user intake of the different ingredients by just entering the foods. The inferred intake levels will then be used to determine the effects of different nutrients on the user during analysis.

Connections.title: Connections
Connections.tooltip: Connections to 3rd party data sources that we can import from.

Connector Imports.title: Connector Imports
Connector Imports.tooltip: A record of attempts to import from a given data source.

Connector Requests.title: Connector Requests
Connector Requests.tooltip: An API request made to an HTTP endpoint during import from a data source.

Connectors.title: Connectors
Connectors.tooltip: A connector pulls data from other data providers using their API or a screenscraper. Returns a list of all available connectors and information about them such as their id, name, whether the user has provided access, logo url, connection instructions, and the update history.

Correlations.title: Correlations
Correlations.tooltip: Examination of the likely effects of a predictor variable on an outcome variable on average for a specific individual

Device Tokens.title: Device Tokens
Device Tokens.tooltip: User token needed to send Android, iOS, or web push notifications.

Join Study.title: Join Study
Join Study.tooltip: By joining this study, you will have the opportunity to gain insights into how the studied factor affects your health and accelerate scientific discovering by anonymously pooling your data.

Manage Reminders.title: Manage Reminders
Manage Reminders.tooltip: Change the settings for your tracking reminders (like notification frequency).

Measurement Exports.title: Measurement Exports
Measurement Exports.tooltip: A request from a user to export their data as a spreadsheet.

Measurement Imports.title: Measurement Imports
Measurement Imports.tooltip: An uploaded spreadsheet or data file to be imported.

Measurements.title: Measurements
Measurements.tooltip: Measurements are any value that can be recorded like daily steps, a mood rating, or apples eaten.

Notifications.title: Notifications
Notifications.tooltip: Tracking reminder notifications, messages, and study results.

Physician Dashboard.title: Physician Dashboard
Physician Dashboard.tooltip: The physician dashboard allows physicians to view their patients data in addition to regularly emailed reports.

Posts.title: Posts
Posts.tooltip: Published studies at the Journal of Citizen Science.

Start Tracking.title: Start Tracking
Start Tracking.tooltip: Going through the onboarding process makes it easy to tracking and discover hidden factors affecting your well-being!

Tracking Reminder Notifications.title: Tracking Reminder Notifications
Tracking Reminder Notifications.tooltip: Specific reminder notification instances that still need to be tracked.

Tracking Reminders.title: Tracking Reminders
Tracking Reminders.tooltip: Manage what variables you want to track and when you want to be reminded.

Unit Categories.title: Unit Categories
Unit Categories.tooltip: Category for the unit of measurement such as weight, rating, distance, or volume.

Units.title: Units
Units.tooltip: Units of measurement such as milligrams or a one-to-five rating scale.

User Tags.title: User Tags
User Tags.tooltip: User-created variable tags are used to infer the user intake of the different ingredients by just entering the foods. The inferred intake levels will then be used to determine the effects of different nutrients on the user during analysis.

User Variables.title: User Variables
User Variables.tooltip: Variable statistics, analysis settings, and overviews with data visualizations and likely outcomes or predictors based on data for a specific individual

Variable Categories.title: Variable Categories
Variable Categories.tooltip: Categories of of trackable variables include Treatments, Emotions, Symptoms, and Foods.

Variables.title: Variables
Variables.tooltip: Variable overviews with statistics, analysis settings, and data visualizations and likely outcomes or predictors based on the anonymously aggregated donated data.

Votes.title: Votes
Votes.tooltip: Vote thumbs down button for relationships that you think are coincidences and thumbs up for correlations with a plausible causal explanation.

oAuth Access Tokens.title: oAuth Access Tokens
oAuth Access Tokens.tooltip: Access tokens are the thing that applications use to make API requests on behalf of a user.

oAuth Clients.title: oAuth Clients
oAuth Clients.tooltip: OAuth clients allow users to permit access to their self-tracking data to the owner of the client.
